$ Stellarium API: core.pauseScript

`core.paused()` pauses the execution of the script. It can be resumed with the → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium#stellarium-shortcut[keyboard shortcut key] that is assigned to `actionResume_Script`. The default
seems to be `ctrl-d r` and can be overwritten in the `config.ini` file (or `%APPDATA%\Stellarium\Config`?).

gh|about-Stellarium|/API/core/pauseScript.ssc||

sa:

  In order to pause a script, `ctrl-d p` can be used

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setTimeRate[`core.setTimeRate(0)`] stops time (but not the script.

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/wait[`core.wait()`]

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API
